Instead of [dropdowns.less#L64](https://github.com/twbs/bootstrap/blob/v3.1.1/less/dropdowns.less#L64):
```
.dropdown-menu {
  > li > a {
    padding: 3px 20px;
  }
}
```

It should be something like this:
```
@dropdown-menu-links-padding-vertical:     @padding-base-vertical/2;
@dropdown-menu-links-padding-horizontal:   @padding-base-horizontal*5/3;

.dropdown-menu {
  > li > a {
    padding: @dropdown-menu-links-padding-vertical
             @dropdown-menu-links-padding-horizontal;
  }
}
```

Same for .dropdown-header padding 3px 20px, see [dropdowns.less#L153](https://github.com/twbs/bootstrap/blob/v3.1.1/less/dropdowns.less#L153).

As a general rule, redifining @padding-base-*, as the name suggests, should IMHO change the default padding of all (most?) Bootstrap elements.
<br>

